ed special apps for telemedicine visits?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Patients simply log in through your branded patient portal or mobile app. Telehealth video consultations run directly inside the Virtual Practice platform — no third-party downloads required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I bill for telehealth visits the same way as in-person consultations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Telemedicine appointments are defined just like in-person services. You can set duration, service charges, and taxes. Patients pay online, and billing records are automatically generated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens to notes from a video consultation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Notes taken during the video consultation are stored in the encounter log. Providers can use them to generate consultation documents, prescriptions, or lab orders. If AI Scribe is used, these notes are included as context for creating smarter clinical documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can more than one person join a telemedicine call?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Providers can invite caregivers, translators, or additional participants for instant video calls. There's also an assisted video mode where nurses or staff help patients in remote areas connect to their provider."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are telehealth video consultations secure and compliant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Absolutely. All telemedicine visits are encrypted and compliant with HIPAA, GDPR, and other healthcare regulations. White-labelling is optional — you can keep the standard Virtual Practice look, or customize the platform and apps to reflect your brand."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What equipment do patients need for telehealth visits?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients just need a smartphone, tablet, or computer with a camera and internet connection. No extra hardware is required for most video consultations."}}]}</script><section class="py-16 bg-gray-50"><div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><div class="text-center mb-12"><h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="w-24 h-1 bg-blue-vibrant mx-auto"></div></div><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8"><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="How do telehealth video consultations work in the Virtual Practice?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">How do telehealth video consultations work in the Virtual Practice?</span><span class="transform transition-transform ">▼</span></button></div><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="Do patients and providers receive reminders about video consultations?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">Do patients and providers receive reminders about video consultations?</span><span class="transform transition-transform ">▼</span></button></div><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="Do patients need special apps for telemedicine visits?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">Do patients need special apps for telemedicine visits?</span><span class="transform transition-transform ">▼</span></button></div><div class="border-b border-gray-200 last:border-b-0"><button aria-label="Can I bill for telehealth visits the same way as in-person consultations?" class="w-full text-left py-4 flex justify-between items-center hover:text-blue-vibrant transition-colors"><span class="font-medium">Can I bill for telehealth visits the same way as in-person consultations?</span><span class="transform transition-transform ">▼<